DATA CLOUD
Pull Activation Data into Data Cloud for Segment Intelligence

To pull Activation data for Segment Intelligence into Data Cloud, create a data stream and map the objects

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience	Available in: Enterprise and Unlimited Editions


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To manage Data Cloud:	Data Cloud Admin permission set
To set up Segment Intelligence:	Data Cloud Admin permission set
Assign the Activation permission set to users who create data streams in Data Cloud.
From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Permission Sets and then select Permission Sets.
Select Data Cloud Salesforce Connector.
Under Apps, select Object Settings.
Search and select Activation Definition.
Click Edit and set the Object Permissions to Read and View All.
Click Save.
Click Manage Assignments.
Click Add Assignments.
Select users that must create data streams with the activation object in Data Cloud.
Click Assign and then click Done.
Users can now see the Activation object in the Data Stream page in Data Cloud.
Create the Activation DMO.
In the Segment Intelligence setup page, go to Installation Prerequisites.
From Pull Activation Data into Data Cloud, under Create the Activation DMO, click Create Activation.
The DMO is created for you.
Create a data stream to pull in activation data.
From the App Launcher, find and select Data Cloud.
On the Data Streams tab, click New.
Select Salesforce CRM and click Next.
On the All Objects tab, find and select Activation.
Click Next.
Under Object Details, for Category, select Other.
Select the data space, and click Deploy.
A new data stream is created that pulls activation data into Data Cloud.
Map the Segment Activation DLO to a DMO.
In Data Cloud, on the Data Lake Objects tab, click Market Segment Activation DLO.
On the right, under Data Mapping, click Start.
Under Data Model entities, click Select Objects.
For Select Objects, select Custom Data Model.
Next to the segment activation link, click the plus icon.
Click Done.
Map the Segment Activation ID field to Segment Activation ID.
Map the Name field to Segment Activation Name.
Map the Segment ID field to Segment ID.
Click Save and Close.
